oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Inspector B
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Inspector B (horse) being held by an African American stable hand.

Inspector B, originally owned by Dwyer Brother Stable, was the 1886 American Champion Three-Year-Old Male Horse. He won both the Belmont Stakes and Travers Stakes in 1886. He later lived at Belle Meade Plantation.
